cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about the evaluation of convolution neural network (CNN) architectures and learning methods on the object categorization problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses learning parameters and classifier design, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The use of CNNs also involves optimization and numerical methods, which could place the paper in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different CNN architectures on the ImageNet dataset, which is a popular benchmark in multimedia and image processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
